items.summary:
Had a slightly confusing conversation a couple of weeks ago with my mom which went something like:
 Me: &ldquo;Oh, the bar exam starts next weekend, &lt;my cousin&gt; is in Manila a week early.&rdquo;
Ma: &ldquo;No, it&rsquo;s this weekend.&rdquo;
Me: &ldquo;That&rsquo;s what I said, next weekend.&rdquo;
Ma: &ldquo;No, this weekend, on the 4th.&rdquo;
Me: &ldquo;That&rsquo;s what next weekend means!&rdquo;
Ma: &ldquo;No, next weekend is the 11th.&rdquo;
 &ldquo;Next weekend&rdquo; is definitely confusing, so I should avoid using it in the future for the much clearer and more definitive &ldquo;this weekend&rdquo; which is unambiguous when used on a weekday.
